@Helen I don't go to the gym that often, but what I've seen is that people do sets at a certain spot, and if someone else is waiting they kinda ask if they want to share it. Most people will be kind enough to take turns with you, but some people like to do all of their sets in a row. It's not a problem to use the same piece of equipment for a long time, but I would reccomend asking someone, if they seem to be waiting, if they would like to share with you. It depends the gym, and what time you go, but there is generally a decent amount of people. A lot of younger people seem to be there later on in the day, and the older ones who have their life in order and can wake up early enough, are there in the morning. Just don't worry about what others think of you. It was very hard when I started going, because I have very bad social anxiety, and have difficulty talking to anyone, but once I started going more, I've noticed that people still judge, and they still give me dirty looks sometimes, but I still smile back at them. When you gain confidence in yourself, everything works a little better. Just keep your head up and don't doubt yourself.
